"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860703","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-20","<p>Public Health England and NHS England developed the first iteration of the cancer dashboard in response to recommendations in the Independent Cancer Taskforce report ‘Achieving world-class cancer outcomes: a strategy for England 2015-2020’. This includes data on breast, colorectal, lung and prostate cancers. Further cancer sites, including blood cancer, were not included because of the risk of making patients identifiable when viewing data for individual hospitals or clinical commissioning groups.</p><p> </p><p>A second iteration of the dashboard is being considered by the National Cancer Transformation Board with a wider ambition to include rarer cancers and cancers with a lower incidence, such a blood cancers, as the dashboard develops.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-03-20T10:45:23.84Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860703/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860703/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860703/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-03-12","Blood Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what plans his Department has to  include blood cancer in the cancer dashboard.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","132060"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860704","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-03-20","<p>The Ministry of Defence remains aware of the recommendations in Lord Lloyd's report. The report was studied carefully at the time and steps were taken to address a number of its key points. The recommendation to set up a fund for ex-gratia payments was not accepted and we have no plans to change this position.</p><p>The UK has undertaken a substantial amount of research into Gulf veteran's illness which concluded that there is no illness which is specific to Gulf veteran's. We continue to keep a watching brief on Gulf illness, but have no plans to institute further research either on causation or clinical management.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","132062 ; 132064","2018-03-20T16:01:35.78Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860704/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860704/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860704/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-03-12","Gulf War Syndrome: Public Inquiries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will implement the recommendations of Lord Lloyd’s report entitled Independent Public Enquiry into Gulf War Illnesses, published in November 2004.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","132061"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860705","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-03-20","<p>The Ministry of Defence remains aware of the recommendations in Lord Lloyd's report. The report was studied carefully at the time and steps were taken to address a number of its key points. The recommendation to set up a fund for ex-gratia payments was not accepted and we have no plans to change this position.</p><p>The UK has undertaken a substantial amount of research into Gulf veteran's illness which concluded that there is no illness which is specific to Gulf veteran's. We continue to keep a watching brief on Gulf illness, but have no plans to institute further research either on causation or clinical management.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","132061 ; 132064","2018-03-20T16:01:35.827Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860705/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860705/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860705/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-03-12","Gulf War Syndrome: Public Inquiries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when he last assessed the findings the Lord Lloyd’s report entitled Independent Public Enquiry into Gulf War Illnesses, published in 2004.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","132062"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860706","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-03-15","<p>VisitBritain and VisitEngland are responsible for promoting the UK as a tourist destination, through a range of different initiatives and campaigns. VisitBritain receive grant-in-aid totalling £19.4m from DCMS and VisitEngland receive £7m. They also receive £22.8m of GREAT funding to support promotion activities. For every £1 the Government has invested in VisitBritain for international marketing, an overseas visitor spends £20 in Britain.</p><p>Additionally, in 2017 VisitBritain participated in travel trade missions across the world such as Destination Britain: China, the World Travel Market, World Routes and Destination Britain: North America. They also hold a variety of domestic promotion events throughout the country.</p>","Northampton North","Michael Ellis",,"2018-03-15T14:53:43.863Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860706/answer","Biography information for Michael Ellis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860706/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860706/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-03-12","Tourism: Marketing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how much money has been spent on promoting British tourism in (a) Europe, (b) Asia, (c) North America and (d) in total in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","132063"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860707","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-03-20","<p>The Ministry of Defence remains aware of the recommendations in Lord Lloyd's report. The report was studied carefully at the time and steps were taken to address a number of its key points. The recommendation to set up a fund for ex-gratia payments was not accepted and we have no plans to change this position.</p><p>The UK has undertaken a substantial amount of research into Gulf veteran's illness which concluded that there is no illness which is specific to Gulf veteran's. We continue to keep a watching brief on Gulf illness, but have no plans to institute further research either on causation or clinical management.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","132061 ; 132062","2018-03-20T16:01:35.733Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860707/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860707/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860707/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-03-12","Gulf War Syndrome: Research","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if his Department will invest in research to improve recovery outcomes for veterans who have from Gulf War Syndrome.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","132064"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860708","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-03-19","<p>The Government is undertaking a wide range of analysis and preparatory work that will contribute to our exit negotiations with the EU, define our future partnership with the EU, and inform our understanding of how EU exit will affect the UK’s domestic policies and frameworks. It is not however standard practice to provide a running commentary on ongoing analysis.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>We are committed to positive and productive engagement with the devolved administrations as we seek a deal that works for the entire United Kingdom.</p>","Fareham","Suella Fernandes",,"2018-03-19T11:28:23.823Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860708/answer","Biography information for Suella Braverman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860708/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860708/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-03-12","Devolution","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, if he will list the independent studies commissioned by his Department on the effect of the UK leaving the EU on the devolved administrations.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Nigel Dodds","132065"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860709","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-03-15","<p>​While we are aware that the Birzeit University Student Council President was arrested on campus on 7 March, we have not raised this issue with the Israeli authorities.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-03-15T17:56:06.697Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860709/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860709/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860709/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-03-12","Israel: Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he has made to his Israeli counterpart on the abduction of the university Student Council President at Birzeit University in the West Bank on 7 March.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","132066"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860710","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-03-19","<p>Ministers across Government have carried out extensive engagement on EU exit with businesses and industry bodies from all sectors of the economy and all regions of the UK. This includes civil society groups such as consumer bodies, trade unions, charities and academia.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>Following the UK’s exit from the EU, arrangements on mobile roaming will be subject to negotiations as part of our future economic partnership. In these negotiations, the Government is committed to securing the best deal on roaming for British consumers.</p><p> </p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2018-03-19T11:27:57.6Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860710/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860710/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860710/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-03-12","Mobile Phones: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what discussions he has had with mobile telephone operators on mobile data roaming charges after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Nigel Dodds","132067"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860711","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-03-15","<p>​While no assessment has been made about this particular issue, we strongly condemn all acts of violence and all incitement to commit acts of violence. We consistently urge Israel to ease movement and access restrictions across the Occupied Palestinian Territories, not least because of the impact the restrictions on continuity of education.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-03-15T17:55:04.627Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860711/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860711/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860711/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-03-12","Israel: Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the levels of (a) violence and (b) harassment towards Palestinian university (i) students and (ii) staff in the West Bank; and what recent assessment he has made of the effect of those levels on student education.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","132068"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860712","Department for International Trade","false","2018-03-20","<p>Estimates of the value (£) and volume (kgs) of UK exports of pharmaceutical and chemical products to the Irish Republic in each of the last five years are available from HM Revenue and Customs ‘Build Your Own Data Tables’ tool at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.uktradeinfo.com/Statistics/BuildYourOwnTables/Pages/Home.aspx" target="_blank">https://www.uktradeinfo.com/Statistics/BuildYourOwnTables/Pages/Home.aspx</a></p><p> </p><p>Estimates by sector are not available.</p>","Beverley and Holderness","Graham Stuart","132070","2018-03-20T15:50:56.79Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860712/answer","Biography information for Graham Stuart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860712/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860712/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-03-12","Exports: Republic of Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what the total amount of exports by (a) volume and (b) value to the Republic of Ireland were in the (i) pharmaceutical and (ii) chemicals sectors in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Nigel Dodds","132069"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860713","Department for International Trade","false","2018-03-20","<p>Estimates of the value (£) and volume (kgs) of UK exports of pharmaceutical and chemical products to the Irish Republic in each of the last five years are available from HM Revenue and Customs ‘Build Your Own Data Tables’ tool at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.uktradeinfo.com/Statistics/BuildYourOwnTables/Pages/Home.aspx" target="_blank">https://www.uktradeinfo.com/Statistics/BuildYourOwnTables/Pages/Home.aspx</a></p><p> </p><p>Estimates by sector are not available.</p>","Beverley and Holderness","Graham Stuart","132069","2018-03-20T15:50:56.837Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860713/answer","Biography information for Graham Stuart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860713/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860713/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-03-12","Imports: Republic of Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what the total amount of imports by (a) volume and (b) value from the Irish Republic were in the (i) pharmaceutical and (ii) chemicals sectors in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Nigel Dodds","132070"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860714","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-03-15","<p>UK support to the Palestinian Authority helps to employ vetted education public servants in the West Bank, including teachers. This enables around 25,000 young Palestinians to receive an education each year. Additionally, UK support to the UN Relief and Works Agency assists in the provision of basic education to around 500,000 children across the region. The UK will continue to urge the Israeli authorities to ease movement and access restrictions across the Occupied Palestinian Territories, not least because of the impact that the restrictions have on children and the continuity of their education.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-03-15T17:57:12.917Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860714/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860714/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860714/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-03-12","Palestinians: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps he is taking to ensure the protection of the right to education in the Occupied Palestinian Territories.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","132071"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860715","Department for International Development","false","2018-03-19","<p>The UK Government has been monitoring the situation in Papua New Guinea since the earthquake on 25 February, in close contact with our counterparts in Australia and New Zealand, who are leading on the well-resourced regional response. DFID has offered support with a child protection psychosocial expert for UNICEF for three months to help children, young people and their families affected by the earthquake.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-03-19T16:39:52.607Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860715/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860715/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860715/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-03-12","Papua New Guinea: Earthquakes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what aid the UK has given to the authorities in Papua New Guinea as a result of the recent earthquake.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Nigel Dodds","132072"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860716","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-03-20","<p>Ofcom and the Phone-paid Services Authority (PSA) are responsible for the regulation of directory enquiry services delivered over the 118 number range (118 services). 118 services have to comply with the PSA’s Code of Practice which is approved by Ofcom and regulates the promotion and operation of Premium Rate Services (PRS) including 118 services. The Code of Practice includes a requirement that consumers of PRS should be fully and clearly informed of all information likely to influence their decision to purchase including cost, before any purchase is made. Companies that breach the Code of Practice can be sanctioned, including in serious cases through fines of up to £250,000 per breach of the Code. Ofcom is responsible for the allocation of 118 numbers and for regulating the tariffs that providers of 118 services may charge.</p><p> </p><p>Following concerns about the rising cost of 118 services, Ofcom launched a review of the cost of calling directory enquiry services in May 2017. Ofcom expects to publish a consultation about the findings of their review and any proposed remedies in spring 2018. In parallel, PSA intends to consult on potential additional consumer protection measures that could be taken under its Code of Practice.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James","132074","2018-03-20T16:23:03.197Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860716/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860716/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860716/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-03-12","Telephone Operator Services: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, if he will bring forward legislative proposals to require 118 directory enquiries phone lines to (a) have an automated message stating the call charges prior to connecting and (b) provide customers an opportunity to terminate a call prior to being connected and charged.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","132073"
