"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860729","Cabinet Office","false","2018-03-21","<p>Of the total floor space occupied by the Cabinet Office 6% is currently rented, 52% is owned and 42% is occupied through other types of agreement (mainly Memorandum of Terms of Occupation, Licences or sub-leases with other government departments).</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2018-03-21T12:36:46.343Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860729/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860729/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860729/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-03-12","Cabinet Office: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what proportion of his Department's estate is (a) rented, (b) owned and (c) occupied through any other type of agreement.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","132086"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860730","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-03-20","<p>The breakdown of DCMS' estate is as follows: 9% rented, 91% occupied by agreement with other government departments. We do not own any of the buildings we occupy or operate from.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-03-20T16:25:56.987Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860730/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860730/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860730/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-03-12","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what proportion of his Department's estate is (a) rented, (b) owned and (c) occupied through any other type of agreement.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","132087"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860731","Department for Education","false","2018-03-15","<p>The National Statistics release ‘Permanent and fixed-period exclusions in England 2015 to 2016’ includes numbers and rates of exclusions. The full release is available here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/permanent-and-fixed-period-exclusions-in-england-2015-to-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/permanent-and-fixed-period-exclusions-in-england-2015-to-2016</a>.</p><p>The local authority tables include exclusion information for Haringey, London and England and the underlying data files include exclusion information at national, regional and local authority level for the 2006/07 academic year and onwards.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","132089","2018-03-15T17:40:40.033Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860731/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860731/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860731/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-12","Pupil Exclusions: Haringey","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many pupil exclusions have been recorded for the London Borough of Haringey in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","132088"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860732","Department for Education","false","2018-03-15","<p>The National Statistics release ‘Permanent and fixed-period exclusions in England 2015 to 2016’ includes numbers and rates of exclusions. The full release is available here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/permanent-and-fixed-period-exclusions-in-england-2015-to-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/permanent-and-fixed-period-exclusions-in-england-2015-to-2016</a>.</p><p>The local authority tables include exclusion information for Haringey, London and England and the underlying data files include exclusion information at national, regional and local authority level for the 2006/07 academic year and onwards.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","132088","2018-03-15T17:40:40.097Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860732/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860732/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860732/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-12","Pupil Exclusions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the pupil exclusion rate is for (a) Haringey (b) London and (c) England.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","132089"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860733","Cabinet Office","false","2018-03-15","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith",,"2018-03-15T12:35:40.2Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860733/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860733/answer","PQ 132090.pdf","PQ 132090.pdf","UKSA Response ","UKSA Response ","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860733/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-03-12","Self-employed","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many people in the UK are self-employed; and what proportion that number is of (a) people in work and (b) the working age population.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","132090"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860734","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-03-15","<p>I am pleased to confirm that 77 projects have taken up our offer of a share of the £1.1 million top up funding and will receive their funding allocations on 22 March 2018. We will publish a full list of the recipients on gov.uk on 22 March 2018.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2018-03-15T16:09:01.867Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860734/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860734/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860734/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-03-12","Refuges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Housing and Homelessness, pursuant to the Answer of 20 February 2018 to Question 127168, on refuges, when her Department plans to announce the allocation of the £1.1million top-up funding.","false","Biography information for Alex Norris","Nottingham North","Alex Norris","132091"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860735","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-03-20","<p>​From 2013 to 2017 the Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) responded to 361 requests for consular assistance from UK nationals who had been arrested for child sex offences. The FCO are not routinely notified of the arrest of all UK nationals overseas. The Vienna Convention on Consular Relations 1963 (Article 36) provides for an embassy to be informed of an arrest only if the individual requests it.</p><p>The attached file contains a breakdown of these arrests by country and year.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-03-20T16:07:59.727Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860735/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860735/answer","PQ 132092 attachment.xlsx","PQ 132092 attachment.xlsx","132092 attachment","132092 attachment","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860735/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-03-12","British Nationals Abroad: Offences Against Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what information his Department holds on the number of UK nationals who have been arrested for child sex offences overseas in the last five years; and in what countries such nationals have been arrested over that period.","false","Biography information for Sarah Champion","Rotherham","Sarah Champion","132092"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860736","Department for Education","false","2018-03-20","<p>As at end of February 2018, there are 117 open AP academies and free schools; 79 are schools that have converted as academies and 38 have opened as new free schools. The tables attached provide figures on the number of these establishments, split by local authority and the year they opened between 2012 and 2018.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-03-20T17:38:00.267Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860736/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860736/answer","Table 1 132093.docx ; Table 2 132093.docx","Table 1 132093.docx ; Table 2 132093.docx","Table 1 ; Table 2","Table 1 ; Table 2","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/860736/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-03-12","Academies: Alternative Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 6 March 2018, to Question 129771 in which local authority the 117 alternative provision academies and free schools are located; for which years between 2013 to 2017 those academies have been open; and whether those such academies are new schools or convert academies.","false","Biography information for Jo Platt","Leigh","Jo Platt","132093"
